jokes: Why do programmers like to celebrate New Year's on 12/31? Because it's 11111 in binary!
What's a computer's favorite New Year's resolution? 1920x1080.
Why did the web developer break up with the server on New Year's Eve? Because of a communication error.
What's a programmer's favorite New Year's Eve song? 'Auld Lang Syne' (for old long strings).
Why do programmers get confused between Halloween and New Year's? Because Oct 31 == Dec 25.
What's a coder's New Year's resolution? To finally comment their code.
Why was the JavaScript developer sad on New Year's Eve? Because he didn't have a date.
What's a programmer's favorite New Year's toast? 'To a year of no more merge conflicts!'
Why did the programmer bring a ladder to the New Year's party? He heard the drinks were on the house.
What's a developer's favorite New Year's movie? 'The Social Network', to remind them of their resolution to be more social.
